It's WordPress with Nginx, php-fpm, MariaDB and PhpMyAdmin based on CentOS 7.

nginx/ — каталог используемый для дополнительной конфигурации Nginx, как виртуального хоста и так далее.
log/ — каталог логов для Nginx, MariaDB и php.
data/ — каталог с файлами WordPress и файлы базы данных.

How to run step-by-step: 

0. Make sure that ports 8080 and 8081 are opened.  
1. Git clone this repo
2. cd /wordpress-compose
3. Create folders: mkdir log && mkdir log/nginx && mkdir data && mkdir data/html &&  mkdir data/mysql
4. Update passwords in docker-compose.yml file
5. docker-compose up -d
(To check logs): 
docker-compose logs nginx
docker-compose logs mysql
docker-compose logs wordpress
6. Go to http://server_IP:8080 for WordPress and to http://server_IP:8081 for phpMyAdmin
